<TITLE> Laptop fair begins in Ctg </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong May 6 (bdnews24.com)  A laptop fair started in the port city on Thursday. The fair, being held in the gymnasium beside M A Aziz Stadium, will run through to Saturday. Chittagong mayor ABM Mohiuddin Chowdhury inaugurated the fair and said the fair would play a significant role in taking technology to the people's doorsteps. He also called for increased use of technology for the development of the country. The media partners of the fair, organised by Maker Communication, are bdnews24.com, Daily Azadi and Radio Today. The organisers said that the stalls will remain open from 10:30am to 8:00pm. The price of the entry ticket is Tk10. Several laptop producers and their local agents are taking part in the fair, being held for the third time in the port city. The organisations taking part are - Executive Technologies, Computer Source, Flora Limited, Smart Technologies, International Office Machines, Computer Valley, Rishit Computers, Excel Technologies, Computer Village, Khan Jahan Ali Computers, Index IT Limited, Grameenphone and Intel Corp. A seminar on information technology will also be held on the second day. Chittagong University's vice chancellor Abu Yusuf, chief editor of bdnews24.com Toufique Imrose Khalidi, president of Bangladesh Computer Society Mostafa Jabbar and advisor to the information and technology ministry Munir Hasan are scheduled to speak at the seminar. Abu Yusuf was the special guest at the inaugural ceremony. Chittagong regional chief of Grameenphone, sponsor of the fair, Jakir Hasan and coordinator Sultan Mahmud also spoke. State minister of law Qamrul Islam is expected to be present as the chief guest in the closing ceremony on Saturday evening. b
